<br>
Frozen in mid step, Kalelce cringes as the squeaky floorboard protests.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Sneaking down the hallway in the sisters guildhall is not so easy.  Good think Kivrin is asleep&quot;<br>
<br>
SNNOORRRKKK<br>
<br>
Kivrin's snore, two rooms away sound like a tundra mammoth calling to her calf.<br>
<br>
Kalelce moves his foot to another spot and continues down the hall.  He finds the room he's looking for, and slips inside, silently closing the latch.<br>
<br>
THUD!!!<br>
<br>
&quot;Marr!&quot;, Kalelce mutters under his breath as he stubs his toe on something in the dark.  Fortunately the accident occurred in the middle of another one of Kivrin?s deep snores.<br>
<br>
Kalelce fumbles around in the dark until he finds the boots.  Taking a jar from his pack, he opens it up, and takes a deep sniff.  &quot;Ah! just right.&quot;<br>
<br>
Pulling out the final pickle, he begins to munch.  Next he pours the remaining juices, into each boot.  Just enough to thoroughly soak the bottom.  He then replaces the jar in his pack, and returns the boots.  Kalelce decides to take a quicker exit, and opens the nearby window. <br>
<br>
&quot;Arania will be surprised!&quot;, Kalelce giggles before falling out the window, landing flat on the ground with a resounding &quot;OAF!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
